",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"test:e2e\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\",\n    \"test:e2e:watch\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --watch --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\",\n    \"test:e2e:cov\": \"jest --config jest-e2e.json --coverage --forceExit --detectOpenHandles\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@nestjs/common\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@nestjs/core\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@nestjs/swagger\": \"^11.4.3\",\n    \"@nestjs/typeorm\": \"^10.0.2\",\n    \"bcrypt\": \"^5.1.1\",\n    \"class-transformer\": \"^0.5.1\",\n    \"class-validator\": \"^0.14.1\",\n    \"reflect-metadata\": \"^0.2.2\",\n    \"rxjs\": \"^7.8.1\",\n    \"typeorm\": \"^0.3.20\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@nestjs/testing\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@types/bcrypt\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.9\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.21\",\n    \"@types/jest\": \"^29.5.12\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20.12.7\",\n    \"@types/passport-jwt\": \"^4.0.1\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.2\",\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.1.2\",\n    \"jest\": \"^29.7.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"ts-jest\": \"^29.1.4\",\n    \"ts-node\": \"^10.9.2\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.5\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Test scripts:** Only e2e tests exist (`test:e2e`, `test:e2e:watch`, `test:e2e:cov`). No unit test script.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `backend/test/jest-e2e.json` — DOES NOT exist at that path.\n\nThe actual jest config is at: **`/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/jest-e2e.json`** (in the `backend/` root, not `backend/test/`).\n\n**Complete content:**\n```json\n{\n  \"moduleFileExtensions\": [\"js\", \"json\", \"ts\"],\n  \"rootDir\": \".\",\n  \"testEnvironment\": \"node\",\n  \"testRegex\": \"test/e2e/.*\\\\.e2e-spec\\\\.ts$\",\n  \"transform\": {\n    \"^.+\\\\.(t|j)s$\": \"ts-jest\"\n  },\n  \"moduleNameMapper\": {\n    \"^src/(.*)$\": \"<rootDir>/src/$1\"\n  },\n  \"globals\": {\n    \"ts-jest\": {\n      \"tsconfig\": \"tsconfig.json\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. `backend/src/app.module.ts` and `backend/src/main.ts` — Both EXIST\n\n### `app.module.ts` (complete — 8 lines):\n```typescript\nimport { Module } from '@nestjs/common';\n\n@Module({\n  imports: [],\n  controllers: [],\n  providers: [],\n})\nexport class AppModule {}\n```\n**State: Empty shell.** No feature modules imported, no TypeORM connection, no global guards/pipes registered.\n\n### `main.ts` (complete — 10 lines):\n```typescript\nimport { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core';\nimport { AppModule } from './app.module';\n\nasync function bootstrap(): Promise<void> {\n  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);\n  app.setGlobalPrefix('api');\n  await app.listen(3000);\n}\n\nvoid bootstrap();\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing test setup files (factories, fixtures, mocks)\n\n### 7a. `test/setup/test-app.factory.ts` (104 lines)\n- **`createTestApp(featureModules)`** — Creates a NestJS test app with **SQLite in-memory** database (`better-sqlite3`, `:memory:`) so no external PostgreSQL is needed.\n- Registers ALL 9 entities directly (User, RefreshToken, PasswordResetToken, Property, PropertyPhoto, Amenity, PropertyAmenity, Favorite, Inquiry).\n- Sets up `ValidationPipe`, `AllExceptionsFilter`, `HttpExceptionFilter`, `LoggingInterceptor`, `TransformInterceptor`.\n- Sets `app.setGlobalPrefix('api')`.\n- Returns `{ app, module }`.\n\n### 7b. `test/setup/test-database.ts` (28 lines)\n- **`cleanDatabase(dataSource)`** — Deletes all rows from all tables in reverse order (FK-safe).\n- **`cleanTable(dataSource, tableName)`** — Deletes rows from a specific table.\n\n### 7c. `test/fixtures/user.fixture.ts` (82 lines)\n- Defines 4 test users: `renter`, `renter2`, `admin`, `suspendedRenter`.\n- Constants: `TEST_PASSWORD = 'TestPass123!'`\n- **`createTestUser(dataSource, userData)`** / **`seedTestUsers(dataSource)`** / **`createUsers(dataSource, users)`**\n\n### 7d. `test/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts` (44 lines)\n- **`generateAccessToken(user)`** → `mock-access-token-{id}-{role}` (placeholder, not real JWT)\n- **`generateRefreshToken(user)`** → `mock-refresh-token-{id}`\n- **`generatePasswordResetToken(user)`** → `mock-reset-token-{id}`\n- **`authHeader(token)`** → `{ Cookie: 'access_token={token}' }` (httpOnly cookie pattern)\n\n### 7e. `test/fixtures/property.fixture.ts` (104 lines)\n- 3 test properties: `downtownApt`, `suburbanHouse`, `cheapStudio`\n- 4 test amenities: Parking, Gym, Pool, Pet Friendly\n- **`createTestProperty()`** / **`seedTestProperties()`** / **`seedTestAmenities()`**\n\n### 7f. E2E test specs (all in RED PHASE)\n- `test/e2e/auth.e2e-spec.ts` — 490 lines\n- `test/e2e/profile.e2e-spec.ts` — 176 lines  \n- `test/e2e/properties.e2e-spec.ts` — 757 lines\n- `test/e2e/favorites.e2e-spec.ts` — 299 lines\n- `test/e2e/inquiries.e2e-spec.ts` — 499 lines\n\nAll e2e specs comment out module imports with `// RED PHASE: These imports will fail because modules don't exist yet.`\n\n---\n\n## 8. `backend/src/core/base/` — Base classes (the 4-layer foundation)\n\n### `base.entity.ts` (20 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseEntity {\n    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')  id: string;\n    @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'timestamp' })  createdAt: Date;\n    @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'timestamp' })  updatedAt: Date;\n    @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })  deletedAt: Date | null;\n}\n```\nAll domain entities **must extend** `BaseEntity`. Soft-delete via `deletedAt`.\n\n### `base.repository.ts` (53 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n    async findAll(options?)    → this.repository.find(options)\n    async findById(id, rels?)  → this.repository.findOne({ where: { id }, relations })\n    async findOne(options)     → this.repository.findOne(options)\n    async create(data)         → repo.create(data) + repo.save(entity)\n    async update(id, data)     → repo.update(id, data) + findById(id)\n    async softDelete(id)       → repo.softDelete(id)\n    async delete(id)           → repo.delete(id)\n    async count(options?)      → repo.count(options)\n}\n```\n\n### `base.service.ts` (57 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseService<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(repository: BaseRepository<T>, entityName: string) {}\n    protected defaultRelations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>;\n    async findByIdOrFail(id, relations?)     // throws NotFoundException\n    async findAll(options?)                   // pass-through to repository\n    async create(data)                        // pass-through to repository\n    async update(id, data)                    // findOrFail + repo.update\n    async remove(id)                          // findOrFail + repo.softDelete\n    async delete(id)                          // findOrFail + repo.delete\n}\n```\n\n### `base.controller.ts` (86 lines)\nGeneric CRUD controller:\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseController<T extends BaseEntity, CreateDto, UpdateDto> {\n    constructor(protected readonly service: BaseService<T>) {}\n    @Post()     async create(createDto) → service.create()\n    @Get()      async findAll(page?, limit?) → service.findAll({ skip, take })\n    @Get(':id') async findOne(id) → service.findByIdOrFail()\n    @Patch(':id') async update(id, updateDto) → service.update()\n    @Delete(':id') async remove(id) → service.remove()\n}\n```\nAll with Swagger decorators (`@ApiOperation`, `@ApiResponse`, `@ApiParam`, `@ApiQuery`) and `ParseUUIDPipe`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Existing auth entities / DTOs in modules\n\n### Auth entities (2 files):\n\n**`refresh-token.entity.ts`** (37 lines) — `@Entity('refresh_tokens')`\n- Fields: `id` (uuid PK), `userId`, `token` (unique varchar 500), `expiresAt`, `revokedAt`, `createdAt`\n- `@ManyToOne → User` (CASCADE delete)\n- Indexed on: `userId`, `expiresAt`\n- **Does NOT extend BaseEntity** (standalone PK, no soft deletes)\n\n**`password-reset-token.entity.ts`** (36 lines) — `@Entity('password_reset_tokens')`\n- Fields: `id` (uuid PK), `userId`, `token` (unique varchar 500), `expiresAt`, `usedAt`, `createdAt`\n- `@ManyToOne → User` (CASCADE delete)\n- Indexed on: `userId`\n- **Does NOT extend BaseEntity**\n\n### User entity:\n\n**`user.entity.ts`** (62 lines) — `@Entity('users')`\n- **Extends `BaseEntity`** (has id, createdAt, updatedAt, deletedAt)\n- Fields: `name`, `email` (unique), `password`, `phone`, `role` (RoleEnum), `status` (UserStatusEnum), `emailVerifiedAt`\n- Relations: `refreshTokens[]`, `resetTokens[]`, `favorites[]`, `inquiries[]`\n- Default role: `RENTER`, default status: `ACTIVE`\n- Indexes: `role+status`, individual `role`, `status`\n\n### Auth DTOs: **NONE exist** — `glob` for `backend/src/modules/**/*.dto.ts` returned zero results.\n\n### Other domain entities:\n\n| Module | Entity | Extends BaseEntity? |\n|--------|--------|---------------------|\n| properties | `Property` | Yes |\n| properties | `PropertyPhoto` | Yes |\n| properties | `Amenity` | Yes |\n| properties | `PropertyAmenity` | No (junction table, composite PK) |\n| favorites | `Favorite` | Yes |\n| inquiries | `Inquiry` | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## Additional supporting files\n\n### `backend/src/config/env-config.service.ts` (97 lines)\n- `EnvConfigService` class wrapping `process.env`\n- Methods: `getPort()`, `isProduction()`, `getFrontendUrl()`, `getOrigins()`, `getTypeOrmConfig()`, `getAuthJWTConfig()`\n- Requires POSTGRES_HOST/PORT/USER/PASSWORD/DATABASE env vars\n\n### `backend/src/config/jwt.config.ts` (16 lines)\n- Exports a config factory reading from `envConfigService.getAuthJWTConfig()`\n\n### `backend/src/infrastructure/token/token.service.ts` (61 lines)\n- `TokenService` using `@nestjs/jwt` and `ConfigService`\n- `getAccessToken(payload, rememberMe?)` — signs JWT with configurable expiry\n- `getRefreshToken(payload)` — signs refresh JWT\n- `verifyToken(token)` / `decodeToken(token)`\n\n### `backend/src/infrastructure/token/token.module.ts` (20 lines)\n- `@Global()` module registering `JwtModule.registerAsync` + `TokenService`\n\n### `backend/src/core/guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts` (37 lines)\n- `JwtAuthGuard extends AuthGuard('jwt')` — respects `@Public()` decorator, delegates to passport JWT strategy\n\n### `backend/src/core/guards/jwt.strategy.ts` (46 lines)\n- Extracts JWT from httpOnly cookie (primary) or Bearer header (fallback)\n- Returns `{ id, email, role }` from token payload\n\n### `backend/src/core/guards/roles.guard.ts` (26 lines)\n- Checks `@Roles(...)` metadata against `request.user.role` (or `user.roles` array)\n\n### `backend/src/core/decorators/` — `@Public()`, `@Roles(...)`, `@CurrentUser()`\n\n### `backend/src/core/filters/http-exception.filter.ts` (51 lines)\n- Catches `HttpException`, returns `{ success, statusCode, message, data, timestamp, path }`\n\n### `backend/src/shared/dtos/response-payload.dto.ts` (143 lines)\n- `ResponsePayloadDto<T>`, `SuccessResponseDto<T>`, `ErrorResponseDto`, `PaginationMetaDto`, `PaginatedResponseDto<T>`\n- All with full Swagger decorators\n\n### `backend/src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts` (42 lines)\n- `PaginationDto` with `page`, `limit`, `sortBy`, `sortOrder`, `search` — all with class-validator decorators\n\n### `backend/src/database/migrations/001-initial-schema.ts` (295 lines)\n- Full raw SQL migration creating all 8 tables (users, refresh_tokens, password_reset_tokens, properties, property_photos, amenities, property_amenities, favorites, inquiries) with indexes and foreign keys\n\n### `backend/tsconfig.json`\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"module\": \"commonjs\", \"target\": \"es2021\",\n    \"experimentalDecorators\": true, \"emitDecoratorMetadata\": true,\n    \"strict\": true, \"strictPropertyInitialization\": false,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true, \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"noEmit\": true, \"outDir\": \"./dist\", \"baseUrl\": \"./\"\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"test\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of project state\n\nThe backend is a **NestJS 4-layer architecture** (Controller → Service → Repository → Entity) with a fully built **core layer** (base classes, guards, filters, interceptors, decorators, pipes). However, **no feature modules are implemented yet**:\n\n| What exists | What's missing |\n|-------------|----------------|\n| 9 TypeORM entities across 4 modules | All controllers, services, repositories |\n| Core base classes (entity, repo, service, controller) | All DTOs (zero `.dto.ts` files) |\n| JWT auth infrastructure (strategy, guard, token service) | All NestJS feature modules (no `.module.ts` in any module) |\n| Test infrastructure (SQLite in-memory, fixtures, e2e specs) | `app.module.ts` registration (empty shell) |\n| Full database migration (001-initial-schema) | Unit tests (no `test:unit` script) |\n| Response DTOs, pagination DTOs, env config | `@nestjs/jwt`, `@nestjs/passport`, `dotenv`, `cookie-parser` dependencies in package.json but not seen in root package.json |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1c03a28cdffeOJrSaFbA8Pp87F","sessionId":"ses_1c039e2d3ffexvTUHVMChGiVGp","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore backend structure","time":{"start":1779186408753,"end":1779186699067}},"id":"prt_e3fc5fcdc001f1xGiRFzrEhqrY","sessionID":"ses_1c03a28cdffeOJrSaFbA8Pp87F","messageID":"msg_e3fc5dada0012wgghfZB0i8MEM"}}
